The paper proposes a new model for tensor completion problem using the tensor ring decomposition and introduces convex surrogates of tensor low-rank assumption on latent tensor ring factors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques such as alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM), which suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments on synthetic and real-world data, which suggests that it could also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
